# ChatGPT → Claude migration toolkit

This toolkit converts a ChatGPT export zip into a reviewable migration package for Claude.

## Requirements

- Python 3.11+ recommended
- `playwright` only if you want browser automation

Install browser automation dependencies only when needed:

```bash
pip install playwright
playwright install chromium
```

## Main capabilities

- parse common ChatGPT export structures, including some alternate JSON filenames
- export conversations to Markdown
- create preview files alongside full exports
- extract attachment-like files from the export zip
- classify extracted attachments into broad categories and summarise them
- extract candidate memory items with confidence, rationale, stale hints, sensitivity flags, and examples
- deduplicate near-duplicate memory items
- group conversations into topic bundles
- generate upload plans, validation reports, manual-attention reports, an HTML summary, and export summaries
- provide a TUI for review, filtering, sorting, and inline memory editing
- track migration progress in `migration_state.json`

## Typical workflow

```bash
python chatgpt_migration_tui.py /path/to/chatgpt-export.zip ./selection.json
python migrate_chatgpt_to_claude.py /path/to/chatgpt-export.zip -o ./out --selection-file ./selection.json
```

## Direct export

```bash
python migrate_chatgpt_to_claude.py /path/to/chatgpt-export.zip -o ./out --token-budget 120000
```

## Search-filtered export

```bash
python migrate_chatgpt_to_claude.py /path/to/chatgpt-export.zip -o ./out --query "kivy British English"
```

## Redaction

```bash
python migrate_chatgpt_to_claude.py /path/to/chatgpt-export.zip -o ./out --redact "sk-[A-Za-z0-9]+" --redact "user@example.com"
```

## Review migration state

```bash
python review_state.py ./out/migration_state.json --mark-uploaded projects/ai.md conversations/0001_test.md --note "Uploaded core bundles"
```

## TUI controls

- `Tab` switch pane
- `↑ ↓` or `j k` move
- `Space` toggle selection
- `/` search current pane
- `t` cycle sort mode
- `g` jump to index
- `p` switch preview mode
- `e` edit current memory item
- `a` select all in current pane
- `n` deselect all in current pane
- `s` save selection file
- `q` quit
- mouse click toggles row
- mouse wheel scrolls

## Generated outputs

- `conversations/`
- `previews/`
- `projects/`
- `attachments/`
- `claude_memory_import.md`
- `claude_memory_import.json`
- `memory_review.tsv`
- `manifest.json`
- `attachments_manifest.json`
- `project_plan.json`
- `migration_strategy.md`
- `migration_state.json`
- `conversation_report.tsv`
- `upload_plan.json`
- `validation_report.json`
- `manual_attention.md`
- `migration_summary.html`
- `browser_automation.py`

## Known limits

- memory extraction is heuristic rather than model-based
- contradiction detection is approximate
- token estimation is approximate
- browser automation is guided and selector-dependent
- unusual ChatGPT export formats may still need parser work

## Skip attachment extraction

```bash
python migrate_chatgpt_to_claude.py /path/to/chatgpt-export.zip -o ./out --no-attachments
```

## Dry run

```bash
python migrate_chatgpt_to_claude.py /path/to/chatgpt-export.zip --dry-run --after 2024-01-01 --before 2025-01-01
```

## Batch large exports

```bash
python migrate_chatgpt_to_claude.py /path/to/chatgpt-export.zip -o ./out --max-conversations 100
```

## Title filters

```bash
python migrate_chatgpt_to_claude.py /path/to/chatgpt-export.zip -o ./out --title-include "kivy" --title-exclude "old"
```

## Disable parts of the export

```bash
python migrate_chatgpt_to_claude.py /path/to/chatgpt-export.zip -o ./out --no-memory --no-projects
```
